        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>
Imaging requirement: 
We only request 1 pointing centered on the nucleus of NGC 1068. The diameter of 
the starburst ring in NGC 1068 is ~30 arcsec, which just fits the Band 3 FoV. 
We don't need ACA(+TP) because we reqired similar maximam recoverable scale, 21" 
as that of cycle 0 observations. The missing flux of cycle 0 data is less than 
20% of single dish flux for the 13CO, which seems to be most extended among the 
observed lines. 

Sensitivity requirement: 
We request a  sensitivity of 1 mJy (1 sigma) at 110GHz,in order to detect the 
GMC-scale (~ 80 pc) molecular clouds. 
We estimate the expected 13CO(1-0) flux in the starburst ring. The cycle 0 data 
cube has a beam size of 4" x 2" with a line sensitivity of 3 mJy (for a velocity 
resolution of 1.3 - 1.5 km/s). The identified GMAs in the cycle 0 data cube (with 
a significance of &gt; 8 sigma) have a typical molecular gas mass of a few x 10^6 Mo 
(Tosaki et al. 2014 in prep.). This means that molecular gas mass is about 3 times 
larger than the typical gas mass of GMCs, ie., it is expected that each GMA identified 
in the cycle 0 data will contain typical 3 GMCs in it. In the proposed cycle 2 
observations, we aim to resolve the GMAs into GMCs. Therefore, we request 1" 
resolution, which corresponds to ~70 pc or typical size of GMCs. In order to detect 
these GMCs with a similar S/N ratio, we need 3 times deeper line sensitivity because 
the GMAs identified in cycle 0 data will be resolved into 3 GMCs, so the expected 
flux per 1" beam will be 1/3 of the measured flux (per 4"x2" beam) in cycle 0. 
It results in a required a line sensitivity of 1 mJy for the same velocity resolution 
as cycle 0. OT says total 12m array time is 5.44 h + 2.72 h. 

Correlator setup: 
In order to detect GMC scale clouds, we employ FDM mode. We require velocity resolution 
of 0.488 MHz or 1.3-1.5 km/s. It is enough to resolve each GMCs. The baseband-2, 3, 4 
is setup with fraction of 1/4 (df ~ 234 MHz). The set up of baseband-1 with full fraction 
(df ~ 937 MHz) is need for observations of both of 13CO and C18O at the same time.

Calibration: 
we do not need any special calibration, including bandpass accuracy. 

Data rate: 
OT says the rate is 9.5 MB/s, which is comfortably below the limit.

Special constraints on standard observing modes: 
No constraints.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
